recitals:
,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 4081/87 of 21 December 1987 opening an annual Community tariff quota for unroasted malt of subheading 1107 10 99 of the combined nomenclature, originating in, and coming from, Finland (1), and in particular Article 2 thereof,
Whereas all Community importers should be ensured access to the annual quota of 2 500 tonnes of malt and the 100 ECU per tonne import levy reduction should be granted without interruption until the quota has been used up;
Whereas this method of management requires close cooperation between the Member States and the Commission, which must, in particular, be able to monitor the state of exhaustion of the tariff quota and inform the Member States thereof;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Cereals,
